On December 17, 2020, the President signed three bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 4975, designates the United States Postal Service facility at 1201 Sycamore Square Drive in Midlothian, Virginia, as the Dorothy Braden Bruce Post Office Building. The second bill, H.R. 5062, designates the United States Postal Service facility at 9930 Conroy Windermere Road in Windermere, Florida, as the Officer Robert German Post Office Building. Lastly, H.R. 5307 designates the United States Postal Service facility at 115 Nicol Avenue in Thomasville, Alabama, as the Postmaster Robert Ingram Post Office.